(173, 127, 'Project Manager', '<p>We are looking for an experienced and motivated Green Energy Project Manager to oversee our green energy projects from inception to completion. This role involves planning, budgeting, coordinating teams, and ensuring projects are completed on time, within scope, and within budget. The successful candidate will play a crucial role in advancing our sustainability goals and promoting the use of green technology.</p>\r\n<h4>Key Responsibilities:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Project Planning</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Develop comprehensive project plans outlining scope, objectives, deliverables, timelines, and resources.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct feasibility studies and risk assessments to ensure project viability.</li>\r\n<li>Establish clear project milestones and performance metrics.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Budgeting and Financial Management</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Create and manage project budgets, ensuring all expenditures are tracked and controlled.</li>\r\n<li>Analyze financial reports and provide regular updates on project financial status.</li>\r\n<li>Identify cost-saving opportunities and optimize resource allocation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Team Coordination and Leadership</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lead cross-functional teams, ensuring clear communication and collaboration among team members.</li>\r\n<li>Assign tasks and responsibilities, monitor progress, and provide support as needed.</li>\r\n<li>Foster a positive and productive work environment, encouraging team engagement and innovation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Stakeholder Management</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Engage with stakeholders, including clients, contractors, and regulatory bodies, to ensure project alignment with their needs and expectations.</li>\r\n<li>Provide regular project updates and reports to stakeholders, addressing any concerns or changes in project scope.</li>\r\n<li>Maintain strong relationships with all project stakeholders to facilitate smooth project execution.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Quality and Compliance</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ensure all project activities comply with relevant regulations, standards, and best practices.</li>\r\n<li>Conduct regular quality assurance checks and implement corrective actions as necessary.</li>\r\n<li>Maintain thorough project documentation and records for audit and review purposes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Continuous Improvement</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Identify opportunities for process improvement and implement best practices in project management.</li>\r\n<li>Stay updated with the latest advancements in green technology and project management methodologies.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in professional development activities to enhance skills and knowledge.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Qualifications:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Education</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor\'s degree in Project Management, Environmental Science, Engineering, or a related field.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Certification</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Project Management Professional (PMP) certification or equivalent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Experience</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minimum of 5 years of experience in project management, preferably in green energy or related industries.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Skills</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Proven ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously.</li>\r\n<li>Strong understanding of project management methodologies and tools.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent leadership, communication, and interpersonal skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to manage budgets and financial reports effectively.</li>\r\n<li>Strong problem-solving and decision-making abilities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Preferred Skills:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>In-depth knowledge of green technology and sustainable practices.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with renewable energy projects such as solar, wind, or bioenergy.</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in project management software such as MS Project, Asana, or Trello.</li>\r\n<li>Strong analytical and strategic thinking skills.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Benefits:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Competitive salary commensurate with experience and qualifications.</li>\r\n<li>Performance-based project bonuses.</li>\r\n<li>Comprehensive health benefits, including medical, dental, and vision coverage.</li>\r\n<li>Retirement savings plan with company match.</li>\r\n<li>Generous paid time off and holiday benefits.</li>\r\n<li>Opportunities for professional growth and career advancement.</li>\r\n<li>A collaborative and innovative work environment committed to sustainability.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Join our team and lead transformative green energy projects that make a positive impact on the environment. Apply today to become a key player in our journey toward a sustainable future!</p>', '180000', '230000', '5', '2024-07-14 10:10:45', 50, 'Contract', 'Negombo', 'Consulting', '2024-09-10'),
(174, 127, 'Energy Analyst', '<p>We are seeking a detail-oriented and analytical Energy Consumption and Efficiency Analyst to join our team. The primary responsibility of this role is to analyze energy consumption patterns, evaluate efficiency measures, and recommend strategies to reduce energy usage. This role is crucial in helping our organization achieve sustainability goals and reduce operational costs through efficient energy management.</p>\r\n<h4>Key Responsibilities:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Data Collection and Analysis</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Collect and analyze data related to energy consumption across various departments and facilities.</li>\r\n<li>Use statistical and analytical tools to interpret data and identify trends and patterns.</li>\r\n<li>Develop and maintain energy consumption databases and ensure data accuracy and integrity.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Reporting and Documentation</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Prepare detailed reports on energy consumption and efficiency, highlighting key findings and insights.</li>\r\n<li>Create visualizations and presentations to communicate data trends and recommendations to stakeholders.</li>\r\n<li>Document energy-saving measures implemented and their outcomes.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Recommendation and Implementation</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Identify opportunities for energy savings and efficiency improvements.</li>\r\n<li>Develop and propose actionable energy-saving measures and strategies.</li>\r\n<li>Collaborate with relevant departments to implement recommended energy-saving initiatives and monitor their effectiveness.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Compliance and Standards</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Ensure compliance with local, state, and federal regulations related to energy consumption and efficiency.</li>\r\n<li>Stay updated on industry standards, best practices, and technological advancements in energy management.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<p><strong>Continuous Improvement</strong>:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Continuously seek opportunities to improve energy efficiency and reduce waste.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in professional development activities to stay current with industry trends and enhance skill sets.</li>\r\n<li>Lead or participate in cross-functional teams to drive energy efficiency projects.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Qualifications:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Education</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor\'s degree in Environmental Science, Energy Management, Engineering, or a related field.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Experience</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Minimum of 2 years of experience in energy analysis, efficiency management, or a related field.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n<li><strong>Skills</strong>:\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Proficiency in data analysis and statistical tools.</li>\r\n<li>Strong understanding of energy consumption metrics and efficiency measures.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent analytical, problem-solving, and critical thinking skills.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to communicate complex data in a clear and concise manner to various stakeholders.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of relevant energy regulations and standards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Preferred Skills:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Advanced skills in data analysis tools such as Excel, SQL, or specialized energy management software.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with energy modeling and simulation software.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of renewable energy sources and sustainable practices.</li>\r\n<li>Strong project management skills and ability to lead energy efficiency projects.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Benefits:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Opportunities for professional development and continuous learning.</li>\r\n<li>Comprehensive health benefits, including medical, dental, and vision coverage.</li>\r\n<li>Retirement savings plan with company match.</li>\r\n<li>Paid time off and holiday benefits.</li>\r\n<li>A collaborative and supportive work environment focused on sustainability and innovation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Join our team and play a vital role in driving our sustainability initiatives and making a positive impact on the environment. Apply today and contribute to a greener and more energy-efficient future!</p>', '90000', '120000', '2', '2024-07-14 10:21:22', 35, 'Part Time', 'Negombo', 'Energy & Utilities', '2024-08-25'),
(175, 126, 'IT Support Intern', '<p><strong>Job Description:</strong><br />We are seeking a proactive IT Support Intern to provide technical support to users and assist with IT projects. This role involves troubleshooting technical issues, maintaining IT equipment, and gaining valuable hands-on experience in the IT field.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Troubleshoot Issues:</strong> Identify and resolve technical issues reported by users, providing timely and effective solutions.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Maintain IT Equipment:</strong> Assist in the setup, maintenance, and repair of IT hardware and software.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Support IT Projects:</strong> Contribute to IT projects by providing technical support and assisting with various tasks as needed.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Currently pursuing a degree in IT or a related field.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Preferred Skills:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Basic knowledge of IT concepts and systems.</li>\r\n<li>Strong communication skills to interact effectively with users and team members.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Hands-on experience in IT support and operations.</li>\r\n<li>Mentorship from experienced IT professionals.</li>\r\n</ul>', '15000', '20000', '0', '2024-07-19 10:28:36', 25, 'Internship', 'Matara', 'Information Technology', '2024-08-20'),
(176, 126, 'Software Tester', '<p><strong>Job Description:</strong><br />We are seeking an experienced Software Tester to join our team and ensure the quality and reliability of our software applications. The role involves testing software for bugs and issues, writing detailed test cases, executing tests, and reporting defects to support the development of high-quality software products.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Write Test Cases:</strong> Develop comprehensive test cases based on requirements and specifications.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Execute Tests:</strong> Perform manual and automated testing to identify and document software defects.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Report Defects:</strong> Accurately report and track defects, working closely with development teams to resolve issues.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in IT or a related field.</li>\r\n<li>2+ years of experience in software testing.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Preferred Skills:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Experience with both manual and automated testing techniques.</li>\r\n<li>Familiarity with testing tools and frameworks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Training opportunities to enhance skills and knowledge.</li>\r\n<li>Flexible working hours to support work-life balance.</li>\r\n</ul>', '80000', '100000', '2', '2024-07-19 10:31:07', 35, 'Part Time', 'Matara', 'Information Technology', '2024-08-25'),
(177, 122, ' IT Support Specialist', '<p><strong>Job Description:</strong> We are looking for a dedicated IT Support Specialist to provide comprehensive technical support and ensure the smooth operation of our IT infrastructure. This role requires expertise in troubleshooting complex issues, managing IT systems, and providing exceptional customer service.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Troubleshoot and Resolve Issues:</strong> Diagnose and resolve hardware, software, and network issues reported by users, ensuring minimal disruption to their work.</li>\r\n<li><strong>System Management:</strong> Oversee the installation, configuration, and maintenance of IT systems, including servers, workstations, and peripherals.</li>\r\n<li><strong>User Support:</strong> Provide assistance to end-users with technical problems, including remote support when necessary.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Documentation and Reporting:</strong> Maintain detailed records of support activities, including issue resolutions and system changes.</li>\r\n<li><strong>Collaborate with IT Team:</strong> Work with other IT professionals to implement improvements and upgrades to the IT infrastructure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Information Technology, Computer Science, or a related field.</li>\r\n<li>Proven experience as an IT Support Specialist or similar role.</li>\r\n<li>Strong understanding of computer systems, mobile devices, and network infrastructure.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Preferred Skills:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Certifications such as CompTIA A+, Network+, or Microsoft Certified Professional (MCP) are advantageous.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent problem-solving skills and ability to work under pressure.</li>\r\n<li>Strong communication skills, with a focus on providing exceptional user support.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Competitive salary with performance-based incentives.</li>\r\n<li>Opportunity to work with cutting-edge technology and tools.</li>\r\n<li>Professional development and training opportunities.</li>\r\n<li>Health and wellness benefits.</li>\r\n</ul>', '70000', '120000', '2', '2024-07-23 13:21:05', 35, 'Full Time', 'Colombo', 'Accounting & Finance', '2024-08-30'),
(178, 126, 'IT Project Manager', '<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p>\r\n<p>We are seeking an experienced IT Project Manager to lead and manage IT projects for our organization in Colombo. The ideal candidate will have a proven track record of delivering complex IT projects on time and within budget. This role requires strong leadership, communication, and organizational skills to ensure successful project outcomes and client satisfaction.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Lead and manage IT projects from initiation to completion, ensuring adherence to project timelines, budgets, and scope.</li>\r\n<li>Develop detailed project plans, including scope, objectives, timelines, resources, and risk management strategies.</li>\r\n<li>Coordinate with cross-functional teams, stakeholders, and clients to ensure clear communication and alignment on project goals.</li>\r\n<li>Monitor and report on project progress, identifying and addressing any issues or risks that may impact project success.</li>\r\n<li>Manage project budgets, track expenses, and ensure financial control throughout the project lifecycle.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure project deliverables meet quality standards and client expectations.</li>\r\n<li>Facilitate project meetings, presentations, and status reports to stakeholders and senior management.</li>\r\n<li>Implement and maintain project management best practices and methodologies.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, Business Administration, or a related field. A Master&rsquo;s degree or relevant certifications (e.g., PMP, PRINCE2) is a plus.</li>\r\n<li>Proven experience in managing IT projects, with a strong understanding of project management methodologies and tools.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent organizational and multitasking skills, with the ability to lead and motivate project teams.</li>\r\n<li>Strong analytical and problem-solving abilities, with attention to detail and accuracy.</li>\r\n<li>Exceptional communication and interpersonal skills, with the ability to effectively engage with stakeholders at all levels.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Preferred Skills:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Experience with project management software (e.g., Microsoft Project, JIRA, Asana).</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of software development life cycle (SDLC) and ITIL framework.</li>\r\n<li>Familiarity with Agile and Scrum methodologies.</li>\r\n<li>Ability to handle multiple projects simultaneously and adapt to changing priorities.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Benefits:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Competitive salary and performance-based bonuses.</li>\r\n<li>Health and wellness benefits, including medical insurance.</li>\r\n<li>Opportunities for professional development and career advancement.</li>\r\n<li>Flexible working hours and remote work options.</li>\r\n<li>Supportive and collaborative work environment.</li>\r\n</ul>', '150000', '250000', '5', '2024-07-28 13:33:16', 45, 'Full Time', 'Matara', 'Information Technology ', '2024-08-31'),
(179, 122, 'Associate Software Engineer', '<p>Job Description: As an Associate Software Engineer, you will be involved in designing, developing, and maintaining software applications. You will work closely with senior engineers to understand requirements and provide technical solutions that meet business needs.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Key Responsibilities:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Develop and maintain software applications.</li>\r\n<li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to define and design new features.</li>\r\n<li>Write clean, scalable, and efficient code.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in code reviews and ensure adherence to coding standards.</li>\r\n<li>Troubleshoot and debug applications.</li>\r\n<li>Assist in the development of technical documentation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.</li>\r\n<li>Proven experience in software development through internships or academic projects.</li>\r\n<li>Strong understanding of programming languages such as Java, C#, Python, or JavaScript.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Preferred Skills:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Familiarity with web development frameworks (e.g., React, Angular, Django).</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of databases and SQL.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with version control systems (e.g., Git).</li>\r\n<li>Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Benefits:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Competitive salary.</li>\r\n<li>Health and wellness benefits.</li>\r\n<li>Professional development opportunities.</li>\r\n<li>Flexible working hours.</li>\r\n<li>Opportunities for career advancement.</li>\r\n</ul>', '90000', '120000', '1', '2024-08-01 17:06:29', 30, 'Full Time', 'Colombo', 'Information Technology ', '2024-08-31'),
(180, 122, 'Junior Developer', '<p>Job Description: The Junior Developer will assist in the development and maintenance of software applications. This role is ideal for recent graduates who are eager to learn and grow in a collaborative environment.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Key Responsibilities:</p>\r\n<p>Write and test code for new software applications.</p>\r\n<p>Modify existing software to fix bugs or improve performance.</p>\r\n<p>Assist in the design and implementation of software solutions.</p>\r\n<p>Participate in team meetings and provide input on technical discussions.</p>\r\n<p>Document software development processes and procedures.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Qualifications:</p>\r\n<p>Bachelor\'s degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.</p>\r\n<p>Basic understanding of programming languages and software development principles.</p>\r\n<p>Experience with programming languages such as Java, C++, or PHP is a plus.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Preferred Skills:</p>\r\n<p>Knowledge of front-end and back-end development.</p>\r\n<p>Familiarity with Agile development methodologies.</p>\r\n<p>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.</p>\r\n<p>Ability to work both independently and as part of a team.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Benefits:</p>\r\n<p>Competitive salary.</p>\r\n<p>Health insurance coverage.</p>\r\n<p>Paid time off and holidays.</p>\r\n<p>Opportunities for professional growth and development.</p>', '60000', '70000', '', '2024-08-01 17:08:51', 28, 'Full Time', 'Colombo', 'Information Technology ', '2024-09-10'),
(185, 126, 'Front End Developer', '<p><strong>About Us:</strong></p>\r\n<p>Sapphire Technologies is a leading technology company dedicated to delivering innovative solutions and exceptional user experiences. We are seeking a talented Front End Developer to join our dynamic team and contribute to creating stunning, responsive web applications.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Collaborate with designers and back-end developers to translate UI/UX design wireframes into functional web applications.</li>\r\n<li>Develop and maintain user-facing features using HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</li>\r\n<li>Optimize web applications for maximum speed and scalability.</li>\r\n<li>Ensure the technical feasibility of UI/UX designs and implement responsive design principles.</li>\r\n<li>Troubleshoot and debug issues to ensure a seamless user experience across different devices and browsers.</li>\r\n<li>Stay up-to-date with emerging web technologies and industry trends to incorporate new techniques into projects.</li>\r\n<li>Write clean, maintainable, and efficient code, following best practices and coding standards.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in Computer Science, Web Development, or a related field (or equivalent experience).</li>\r\n<li>Proven experience as a Front End Developer or similar role.</li>\r\n<li>Proficiency in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with front-end frameworks such as React, Angular, or Vue.js.</li>\r\n<li>Familiarity with version control systems like Git.</li>\r\n<li>Knowledge of responsive design principles and cross-browser compatibility.</li>\r\n<li>Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.</li>\r\n<li>Excellent communication and teamwork skills.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>Preferred Skills:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Experience with CSS pre-processors like Sass or LESS.</li>\r\n<li>Familiarity with build tools and task runners such as Webpack, Gulp, or Grunt.</li>\r\n<li>Understanding of RESTful APIs and integration.</li>\r\n<li>Experience with UI/UX design tools such as Sketch, Figma, or Adobe XD.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><strong>What We Offer:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Competitive salary and benefits package.</li>\r\n<li>Opportunities for professional growth and development.</li>\r\n<li>Collaborative and inclusive work environment.</li>\r\n<li>[Any additional perks or benefits Sapphire Technologies offers].</li>\r\n</ul>', '65000', '75000', '0', '2024-08-09 15:30:37', 30, 'Full Time', 'Colombo', 'Information Technology', '2024-08-25');

